==========================================

This change was developed after Step 08 (PR #9, still open) in the same session;
it is stacked on the feat/step-08-polish-docs branch because it builds on that
branch's keys.go changes.

[1] Ok, is there a way to mark all items from a source read? If not, could we
    plan that out?
    (plan mode) -- Explore agents found the store already supports source scoping:
    model.Filter has SourceIDs, and store.Query + store.MarkAllRead both translate
    it via the shared buildWhere helper (source_id IN (...)). So no UI action
    existed, but the plumbing did -- the feature was pure UI wiring.

[2] AskUserQuestion -- "Entire source": S marks every item from the source read,
    ignoring the active filter (the literal "all items from a source"), rather than
    source + current filter.

[3] (ExitPlanMode) plan approved.

